frameDefinitions: A Protagonist has (or does not have) a Weapon.
A Location is filled or covered with the Theme.
These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
A piece of Ammunition is a disposable artifact to be fired as a projectile in a weapon with the purpose of causing harm or damage.
These are words relating to filling containers and covering areas with some thing, things or substance, the Theme.
frameExamples: Apparently, the suspect is <t>armed</t> with a shotgun.
The waters of the bay <t>teemed</t> with fish.
The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
The octagenarian inventor's vest repels armor-piercing <t><fex name='amm'>bullets</fex></t>.
Lionel Hutz <t>coated</t> the wall with paint.
listRoleDefinitions: The destructive device that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has with them.
The individual that possesses a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The location where a <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> covers or fills the <fen>Location</fen>.  This role most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with or in.
<fen>Location</fen> is the object or area that the <fen>Theme</fen> fills or covers.  This frame element generally occurs as the External Argument.
The period of time during which the the Abounding_with event occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Ammunition</fen> that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor who instigates the filling.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the physical object or substance which changes location.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is the area or container being filled. Goal is generally the NP Object in this frame.
An event which brings about the filling of the <fen>Goal</fen>.
When the filling occurs.
Where the filling takes place.
listRoleExamples: The waters of the bay teemed <fex>with fish</fex>.
<fex>The walls</fex> crawled with nanite surveillance probes.
<fex>A basic washing</fex> can degrease your workclothes.
The prisoners were deloused <fex>in June and August</fex>.
Rev. Lovejoy carefully brushed the rolls <fex>with butter</fex>.
